inlineContent.text: properties and methods to retrieve media items (tracks) and playlists from the user’s iTunes library.
also provides methods for extracting artwork from a media file that may or may not be in the iTunes library. Sandboxed and nonsandboxed apps can also use iTunes’ ability to extract artwork.
A person needs to grant your app permission before it can access their iTunes library. Add the
file, and include a description of how you intend to use their library. If this key isn’t present, the system terminates your app when it tries to access the library.
